<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,988,1594]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
This species group is newly proposed to include one species previously part of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1322,989,1015]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halabala">
<emphasis box="[1170,1322,989,1015]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ph. halabala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2011" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" box="[199,476,1025,1051]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[199,314,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ph. satun</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber B. A." box="[324,476,1025,1051]" journalOrPublisher="Bonner zoologische Monographien" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 509" part="58" refString="Huber B. A. 2011. Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien 58: 1 - 509." title="Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae)" type="journal article" year="2011">Huber, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), one species previously tentatively assigned to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1319,1025,1051]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ethagala">
<emphasis box="[1111,1319,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pholcus ethagala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2011" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" box="[199,578,1061,1087]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri">
<emphasis box="[199,419,1061,1087]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ph. schwendingeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber B. A." box="[428,578,1061,1087]" journalOrPublisher="Bonner zoologische Monographien" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 509" part="58" refString="Huber B. A. 2011. Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien 58: 1 - 509." title="Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae)" type="journal article" year="2011">Huber, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and a newly described species (
<taxonomicName authority="Huber" authorityName="Huber" box="[978,1207,1061,1087]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buatong" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[978,1123,1061,1087]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ph. buatong</emphasis>
Huber
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1221,1317,1061,1087]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). They share three putative synapomorphies, (1) the complete reduction of distal anterior apophyses on the male chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[390,494,1133,1160]" captionStart="Figs 154 – 158" captionStartId="40.[189,241,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[197,1392,476,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[194,1393,476,1855]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 154 – 158. Pholcus buatong Huber, sp. nov., ZFMK Ar 15045. 154 – 155. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrow points at whitish membranous structure). 156. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 157 – 158. Cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. Abbreviations: a = appendix; b = genital bulb; e = embolus; p = procursus. Scale lines: 0.3 mm (156), 0.5 mm (154 – 155, 157 – 158)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183721/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
); (2) the very distinctive dorsal bulging of the male palpal patella (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1393,1133,1160]" captionStart="Figs 154 – 158" captionStartId="40.[189,241,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[197,1392,476,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[194,1393,476,1855]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 154 – 158. Pholcus buatong Huber, sp. nov., ZFMK Ar 15045. 154 – 155. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrow points at whitish membranous structure). 156. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 157 – 158. Cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. Abbreviations: a = appendix; b = genital bulb; e = embolus; p = procursus. Scale lines: 0.3 mm (156), 0.5 mm (154 – 155, 157 – 158)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183721/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
; angle between femur and patella ~120–125° rather than ~180° as in typical pholcids); and (3) the large, heavily sclerotized ‘knob’ on the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[725,955,1205,1232]" captionStart="Figs 184 – 192" captionStartId="45.[189,241,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,647,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1399,647,1889]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Figs 184 – 192. Female genitalia, untreated in ventral view, cleared in ventral and dorsal views. 184 – 186. Pholcus buatong Huber, sp. nov. 187 – 189. Ph. satun Huber, 2011. 190 – 192. Ph. schwendingeri Huber, 2011." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183729/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 184, 187, 190</figureCitation>
). The group is strongly supported by preliminary molecular data (A. Valdez-Mondragón, B.A. Huber &amp; D. Dimitrov unpublished data). 
<taxonomicName box="[189,463,1278,1304]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri">
<emphasis box="[189,463,1278,1304]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pholcus schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[523,667,1278,1304]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buatong" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[523,667,1278,1304]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ph. buatong</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[676,768,1278,1304]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
also share a distinctive whitish membranous process retrolatero-distally on the procursus (arrows in 
<figureCitation box="[767,875,1314,1341]" captionStart="Figs 154 – 158" captionStartId="40.[189,241,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[197,1392,476,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[194,1393,476,1855]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 154 – 158. Pholcus buatong Huber, sp. nov., ZFMK Ar 15045. 154 – 155. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrow points at whitish membranous structure). 156. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 157 – 158. Cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. Abbreviations: a = appendix; b = genital bulb; e = embolus; p = procursus. Scale lines: 0.3 mm (156), 0.5 mm (154 – 155, 157 – 158)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183721/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 155</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[891,939,1314,1340]" captionStart="Figs 173 – 183" captionStartId="44.[189,241,1789,1815]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,288,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[189,1399,288,1748]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Figs 173 – 183. Pholcus schwendingeri Huber, 2011, ZFMK Ar 15051 – 52. 173 – 174. Male prosoma, oblique and frontal views. 175. Female prosoma, frontal view. 176. Male eye triad. 177. Process between male eye stalks. 178 – 179. Right genital bulb and procursus, prolateral and dorsal views. 180. Left palp, retrolateral view (arrow points at whitish membranous structure). 181. Male gonopore. 182. Epigynum, ventral view. 183. FemaleALS. Abbreviations: a = appendix; b = genital bulb; e = embolus; p = procursus; tr = trochanter. Scale lines: 10 µm (183); 20 µm (177); 50 µm (181); 80 µm (176); 200 µm (175, 178 – 180, 182); 400 µm (173 – 174)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183727/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">180</figureCitation>
). Otherwise this group appears rather inhomogeneous: 
<taxonomicName box="[389,661,1350,1376]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwendingeri">
<emphasis box="[389,661,1350,1376]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pholcus schwendingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have extremely long eye stalks (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1213,1350,1376]" captionStart="Figs 173 – 183" captionStartId="44.[189,241,1789,1815]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,288,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[189,1399,288,1748]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Figs 173 – 183. Pholcus schwendingeri Huber, 2011, ZFMK Ar 15051 – 52. 173 – 174. Male prosoma, oblique and frontal views. 175. Female prosoma, frontal view. 176. Male eye triad. 177. Process between male eye stalks. 178 – 179. Right genital bulb and procursus, prolateral and dorsal views. 180. Left palp, retrolateral view (arrow points at whitish membranous structure). 181. Male gonopore. 182. Epigynum, ventral view. 183. FemaleALS. Abbreviations: a = appendix; b = genital bulb; e = embolus; p = procursus; tr = trochanter. Scale lines: 10 µm (183); 20 µm (177); 50 µm (181); 80 µm (176); 200 µm (175, 178 – 180, 182); 400 µm (173 – 174)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183727/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 173</figureCitation>
) while males of the other two species have short eye stalks (
<figureCitation box="[705,808,1386,1413]" captionStart="Figs 154 – 158" captionStartId="40.[189,241,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[197,1392,476,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[194,1393,476,1855]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 154 – 158. Pholcus buatong Huber, sp. nov., ZFMK Ar 15045. 154 – 155. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrow points at whitish membranous structure). 156. Male chelicerae, frontal view. 157 – 158. Cleared female genitalia, ventral and dorsal views. Abbreviations: a = appendix; b = genital bulb; e = embolus; p = procursus. Scale lines: 0.3 mm (156), 0.5 mm (154 – 155, 157 – 158)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183721/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName box="[830,1028,1386,1412]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buatong" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[830,1028,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pholcus buatong</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1036,1127,1387,1413]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is rock-dwelling while the other two species are leaf litter dwelling; 
<taxonomicName box="[715,880,1423,1449]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[715,880,1423,1449]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pholcus satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has small 
<collectionCode box="[1002,1070,1423,1449]" collectionName="USA, Florida, Gainesville, University of Florida, Florida Museum of Natural History, Allyn Museum" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">AME</collectionCode>
, while the other two species lack 
<collectionCode box="[246,315,1459,1485]" collectionName="USA, Florida, Gainesville, University of Florida, Florida Museum of Natural History, Allyn Museum" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">AME</collectionCode>
; 
<taxonomicName box="[330,498,1459,1485]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satun">
<emphasis box="[330,498,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pholcus satun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have only one bulbal process (sclerotized embolus), while males of the other two species have a membranous embolus plus an appendix. In all three species, egg-sacs are carried in front of the body (
<figureCitation box="[534,701,1531,1558]" captionStart="Figs 143 – 152" captionStartId="38.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,536,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[217,1371,536,1819]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Figs 143 – 152. Live specimens, Pholcus buatong Huber, sp. nov. (143 – 146), Ph. satun Huber, 2011 (147 – 149), and Ph. schwendingeri Huber, 2011 (150 – 152). 143 – 145. ♂♂ and ♀ from Tham Buatong, Thailand. 146. ♂ from Tham Khao Phueng, Thailand. 147 – 149. Adult ♂, penultimate instar ♂, and ♀ from Gunung Jerai, Malaysia. 150 – 151. ♂♂ from Khao Sok, Thailand. 152. ♀ with egg-sac, from Phanom Bencha, Thailand." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183717/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 145, 152</figureCitation>
) as in typical pholcids. This species group is known from southern Thailand and northern mainland Malaysia (
<figureCitation box="[805,908,1567,1594]" captionStart="Fig. 153" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1329,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1399,1329,1925]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 153. Known distributions of the Pholcus buatong species group (Malay Peninsula) and of the Pholcus andulau species group (northern Borneo)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1183719/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
